metadata.name: Last Leaf
metadata.description:
I will never forget the good feeling that morning when I took this photo.
My fingers were frozen and I was breathing cold air.
It was the beginning of a beautiful winter.
Years have passed and I have not seen such a scene again.
A single beautiful leaf on a branch of a tree.
When something gets lonely becomes beautiful and shows its true self.
I remember this quote:
ALL GREAT AND PRECIOUS THINGS ARE LONELY. (John Steinbeck)
